	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f102553998440374>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Some basic warrior info</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Jul 1st 12:23 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=128466><span id= >angminas</span></a><br><span id=notbold>133 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.62]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Wow, I see a lot of misconceptions on this page. I'll try to toss along some helpful info in this post, rather than making 800 invididual replies. This comes from a lot of personal experience, research, and discussion with other warriors.<br><br>Damage isn't everything as a grouping warrior- taunt is. Sometimes taunt comes from speed...sometimes it comes from damage...don't let anyone tell you that one ALWAYS beats the other, but usually speed is better. In your teens and early twenties, use a fast weapon in offhand to work on the slow-raising dual wield and double attack...then reverse it to prepare for the damage bonus and increased need for taunt that start to show up in your late twenties. Damage bonus on one-handed weapons is calculated as:<br><br>DB = (level-25)/3<br><br>So your damage bonus at level 49 is<br><br>(49-25)/3 = 8<br><br>Two-handed weapons get much more complicated, and you won't need to use them as much, so I'll skip that discussion here. Remember to do all calculations in parentheses first. By 40ish, having a very fast weapon in your main hand will be very important...stop using that Wurmslayer or Centi Longsword. CLS in offhand is okay, but remember that the people who say ratio is all that matters in offhand are mistaken...speed there helps taunt almost as much as it does in main hand. Jade Mace is a good choice in main hand at this level...consider a Fungus Encrusted Hammer, Viik's Dark Defender, Lamentation, or Venom Axe in offhand. Don't let anybody tell you a Lammy does more damage than a Jade Mace...they're completely mad. A Jmace in main hand will outdamage a Lammy by over 5% at level 60, along with greater taunt from the speed...that's after adjusting for the paltry +6str from the Lammy. Remember, though, a Lammy is lighter and adds HP...it's kinda a tossup.<br><br>Haste is your buddy. Few weapon changes are going to add over 20% to your damage output (and taunt! don't forget taunt!) like most haste items will. If you're ~35+ and don't have a haste item, get one. Don't fall into the trap of thinking that AC and stats in one slot are going to be better for you than haste...AC is only worthwhile if you're getting hit, and a ~35+ warrior with no haste is far from maximizing his/her potential. Be careful about listening to haste percentages, because many people don't know what they are talking about. Also, there are two different ways of calculating haste...the most common one is by increase in total number of attacks. That is, if you have a FBSS equipped, you'll do about 21% more damage over time. This does not mean your weapons will be 21% faster! Some people do talk about haste in terms of lower delay, mostly because it's easier to calculate it that way...but it's not the generally accepted way, so there's no real point in using it. It just confuses people with the different numbers and leads to endless arguments.<br><br>Work on all your weapon skills, even Hand to Hand. You never know when you're going to have a use for them, and being able to use a giant hammer as well as a dagger is good for the confidence level. Nobody likes passing up a good deal because it'd take you a year to learn the skill because you didn't work on it from the beginning.<br><br>Procs are just plain complicated. They are nice and helpful, but you can't depend on them for taunt and such, unless you have a shaman giving you 200+ dexterity. Most worthwhile proc weapons don't pop until 50+, and most of them end up being fairly slow for a warrior of that level to use...again, unless you have massive dexterity to make them proc enough to overcome that problem. Another problem with procs is that they can be partially or fully resisted, just like regular spells. If you're fighting mostly yellows and reds, your procs aren't going to do much damage...however, remember that the taunt from any spell is fully applied, even if the target resists. So...if you're using a weapon for a taunt proc (like slow perhaps) and it keeps getting resisted, don't think that makes the weapon worthless. The main kinds of procs in approximate descending order of taunt value are slow, debuff, snare, stun, dot, lifetap, and dd. I haven't noticed self-buff procs to ever create any taunt, personally.<br><br>Soloing: it can be done if you follow a few guidelines. You'd better have a troll or iksar unless you like sitting on your buttocks. I'd also strongly suggest getting some kind of regen item when you can...Ceremonial Iksar Chestplate is the cheapest, usually called Iksar regen bp or some variation thereof. Bind wound is your friend- keep your skill up, and keep plenty of bandages on hand, especially when far from home. Don't try to work on raising neglected weapon skills while soloing. Always know where the nearest zone is. Pull from a distance...try to keep sow on...pull to a safe place, preferably along a zone wall. An add is likely to mess up your day. When soloing, forget taunt and go straight for maximum damage...when soloing, the damage output of your weapons far exceeds any stats, AC, HP, etc. that they might have. The reason for this is that the mob is beating on you as long as it's alive and not running...beating it down faster means you take less damage, and a weapon would have to have some monstrous AC to make up for even a small deficiency in damage output. Soloing effectively ~40+ is very difficult, because it generally requires specialized and expensive gear, such as a Fungus Covered Scale Tunic (regen), Rune Blade (procs a damage absorber), Truncheon of Doom (procs slow at 50), etc. The damage and HP of mobs at this level are so high that you're just overmatched in a slugfest. Soloing a warrior 50+ is virtually impossible.<br><br>When buying or trading for gear, go for maximum efficiency. Weapons are more important than armor...they determine 95% of your damage and taunt. Don't spend half your money on a nice +10str bracer when what you really need is to save for a better 1hs or a haste item. Also, you'll usually want to keep your money spread out...you often get better results from buying several items than from buying one nice item (again, unless it's a weapon). Before buying, be absolutely sure that you can equip the item you want...if it has a proc or click effect, find out for sure what level you need to be to use it. Remember that any unneeded value in your bag is lost efficency. For example, if you have a 30/40 2hs weapon that's worth 2k, sell it buy a Sarnak Battlehammer (warrior only 2hb), which has the same stats but is much cheaper. Then you can use the saved money for an armor upgrade or whatever. Just by using an unpopular weapon skill (you did keep your 2hb up like I told you, right?), you've saved yourself 1.5k or more, while getting the same combat performance. Then buy a BABS or something fairly cheap to keep your 2hs up, and put the extra into a needed slot, like perhaps that nice bracer ^_^ \/<br><br>There is no such thing as a set DPS. If somebody just flat says &quot;the ratio on Hammer of Breaking Stuff is 10/30, so your DPS is 10&quot;, they're mistaken. Same for talking about an &quot;average hit&quot;. These things are affected by your level, damage bonus, haste, weapon skill, strength, which hand the weapon is in, etc. As these things go up, so does your DPS or average hit. Talking about them out of context is just going to spread false info and confuse people. For a good damage calculator, try Luthair's:<br> <a href="http://www.geocities.com/luthairsite/weaponCalc.html" target=_new>http://www.geocities.com/luthairsite/weaponCalc.html</a><br><br>Well, that's all I can think of for now. I'll post more some other time. Travel safely, and bash well!<br><br>Teriuk Blackarrow<br>Warrior<br>Morell-Thule<br>&quot;Greetings %T, have you seen the Can Of Whoop Ass I just got out?&quot;</p>&nbsp;<br>Marshall Teriuk Blackarrow<br>Flames of Vengeance<br>Morell-Thule</td></td></tr>
