	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Scholar>Yosa</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>194 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.56]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You are right there are alot of misconceptions on this page, some of which are in your post.<br><br>1. Damage = Taunt. Plane and simple.&nbsp;&nbsp;Only when the damage being done by two different tanks is almost equil does the number of touches come into play.  Yes both damage and number of touches are factors in determaining who holds agro (and there are others) but damage is the major factor.  If this is not the case please explane how a wiz gets agro after touching the mob only once?  Also explane why a poision base dot will pull agro when a sickness base dot will not.  They both do damage to the mob at the same time intervel.  The only differance being the one dose considerable more damage each &quot;touch&quot;<br><br>2. DPS and Avg Hits.<br>DPS and avg hits are as real as raito.  They are methoods of compairing two diffrent weapons or sets of weapons.  <br>According to the damage calculator you use, at lvl 40 the JM will do 96% of the damage of a Wurmy.  According to dps calculations the JM will do 93% of the damage of the Wurmy.  A differance of 3%.  So it would appear that well over 90% of the damage you do is a function of the dps of the weapon (with the damage bonus calculated in).  This is more than good enough to use in comparing weapons, and in deciding if you get enough more from a considerd up grade to justify the cost.  <br>Since my dps calculation is based on avg hits, these too can be used in determaining the weapons relative effectivness.  <br><br>I used the damage calcular you linked to check a number of the statments about differant weapons I have made on this page and elsewhere.  I didn't find one that the damage calcular give a differnt result than my dps calculations.  <br><br>Other than that I thougt your post was very good.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
