	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=100518><span id= >Meirril</span></a><br><span id=notbold>204 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.52]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Yes damage generates taunt. But you yourself acknowledge that more touches generate more agro if the ammount of damage done is aproximately the same. DOT spells generate an inordnant amount of agro for the damage done. Why? Because the damage is applied every second. I'm sure if you had a wizard nuking and a druid using dots doing the same amount of damage over a minuite, the mob would be all over the druid. <br>While the amount of damage done generates a substantial amount more agro than touches, if you can get almost the same amount of damage done but with twice the amount of hits in the same period of time, I'd suggest the greater number of hits. Why? Because if your the main tank, you'll do just about anything to get the extra agro. If all you want is damage output because your not the main tank, well, I'm not talking about you here.<br><br>Oh, and the one thing alot of people seem to be neglecting in their advice: while weapons are all your flash and bang, just weapons alone do not make the warrior. AC is king! Before stats and/or bonus hit points, go for higher AC. At least until you manage to get up to 1100 AC. Higher AC means less damage per hit wich means that the healer dosen't waste as much mana healing which means everyone keeps killing and not dying. It's much better for something to die faster than getting hit for less, but let's face facts: your going to get hit. Most people consider that your job. And if your AC sucks for your level YOU suck. Spend some time and try to hunt for your armor as much as possible (you'll probably want to save the cash for better weapons, good weapons are generaly cheeper than armor of the same caliber, easier to find for sale, and you need to fill 13 slots with armor, as opposed to 2 slots for weapons, and a range slot that could go either way.). At lower levels it's not that hard to find decent armor for sale at cheep prices IF you head to the right zones (i.e. where it drops, and where those people go to sell the stuff to merchants). After bronze armor though, unless your making a twink your looking at getting armor from drops and trades. <br><br>Hope this makes some sense,</p>&nbsp;<br>Meirril, Fennin Ro</td></td></tr>
